        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 2:29AM CDT by NWS Quad Cities IA IL</headline>
        <description>At 228 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Seaton, or near Aledo, moving quickly northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could cause minor tree limb damage and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Aledo, Burgess, Viola, and Shale City around 235 AM CDT.
New Windsor, New Windsor, and Cable around 245 AM CDT.
Orion, Andover, and Lynn Center around 255 AM CDT.
Cambridge around 300 AM CDT.
Geneseo around 310 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Henry County
Fairgrounds, Ophiem, German Corner, Wanlock, Swedona, Sunny Hill,
Gilchrist, Sunbeam, Ogle, and Old Gilchrist.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 80 in Illinois between mile markers 11 and 29.
Interstate 74 in Illinois between mile markers 15 and 32.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
